claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
detecting an event associated with a mobile device;
in response to the event, producing, by the mobile device, a sensory output indicating the event;
determining a pattern in the sensory output;
emitting light that substantially simulates the determined pattern in the sensory output while concurrently producing the sensory output; and
returning to a normal mode of emission once the sensory output has terminated.

8. A device, comprising:
a light emission module;
one or more processors;
a storage medium; and
instructions stored in the storage medium and configured for execution by the one or more processors, the instructions comprising instructions to:
detect an event associated with a mobile device;
in response to the event, producing, by the device, a sensory output indicating the event;
determining a pattern in the sensory output produced;
emitting light that substantially simulates the determined pattern in the sensory output while concurrently producing the sensory output; and
returning to a normal mode of emission once the sensory output terminates.

14. A computer program product, encoded on a machine-readable storage device or substrate, operable to cause a data processing apparatus comprising a light-emitting device to perform operations comprising:
detecting an event associated with a mobile device;
in response to the event, producing, by the mobile device, a sensory output indicating the event;
determining a pattern in the sensory output produced;
emitting light that substantially simulates the determined pattern in the sensory output while concurrently producing the sensory output; and
returning to a normal mode of emission once the sensory output terminates.

20. A system, comprising:
means for detecting an event associated with a mobile device;
means for, in response to the event, producing a sensory output indicating the event;
means for determining a pattern in the sensory output;
means for interrupting a normal mode of emission that emits a normal mode light effect, the normal mode light effect conveying particular device information, and initiating an event mode;
means for emitting, in response to the initiation of the event mode, a different event mode light that substantially simulates the determined pattern in the sensory output; and
means for returning to the normal mode of emission following the event mode light effect.

21. A method comprising:
detecting an event;
interrupting a normal mode of emission and switching to an event mode of emission, where the normal mode conveys specified device information using an emission of a particular normal mode light effect;
determining a pattern in the event mode of emission;
in response to switching to the event mode of emission, emitting an event mode light that substantially simulates the determined pattern in the event mode of emission; and
exiting the event mode of emission and returning to the normal mode of emission.
